  "prompt": "Can a person with zero income get a PAN card? What are the necessary conditions to get it?",
  "response": "Yes, a person with zero income can still obtain a PAN (Permanent Account Number) card in India. Here are the necessary conditions and steps:\n\nConditions for obtaining a PAN card:\n1. Indian citizen\n2. Any age group (including minors)\n3. No minimum income requirement\n4. Valid identity proof\n5. Valid address proof\n\nDocuments required:\n1. Proof of Identity (any one):\n- Aadhaar card\n- Passport\n- Voter ID\n- Driving License\n- School/College ID\n\n2. Proof of Address (any one):\n- Aadhaar card\n- Passport\n- Utility bills\n- Bank statement\n- Rent agreement\n\n3. Proof of Date of Birth (any one):\n- Birth certificate\n- Passport\n- School leaving certificate\n- 10th standard mark sheet\n\nApplication methods:\n1. Online through NSDL website\n2. Online through UTI PAN service\n3. Offline through designated PAN service centers\n4. By filling Form 49A\n\nFees:\n- Online application: \u20b9107 (including GST)\n- Offline application: \u20b9110 (including GST)\n\nNote: Even with zero income, a PAN card is useful for various purposes like opening bank accounts, getting mobile connections, etc.",
